data.description: Imagine living in the much sought after community of Victoria Hills. This beautiful and much adored Golf Community can be your new home. This Kolter "Beach Model" is available to be your dream home. Views out from the Lanai are amazing. They overlook the entire community. You are situated on a green belt. The home has too many upgrades and options to describe them all herein. The owner has spent tens of thousands of dollars upgrading the home. There are 3 BR, 3.5 Bath, and a Den. Plus, Kitchen, Dinette, Great Room, Formal Dining, a covered Lanai and huge covered front porch. The common rooms all have custom porcelain tile wood grain floors. Starting at the rear of the home you have the perfect open concept entertainment home. You can party with 50 or more and not even think you're crowded. The Kitchen has the following features: walk-in Pantry, wet island, tear drop style lights over the island, island seating for 3, can lighting over the rest of the kitchen, 9 foot ceilings, 42 inch custom cabinets, dinette with light fixture, stunning quartz counter tops, Energy Star Stainless Steel appliances including a hybrid dishwasher, refrigerator, crown moldings, subway tile back splash, butler pantry between the kitchen and formal dining, natural gas oven, gas range, and Stainless Steel double sink. The great Room is Huge. You can install a full entertainment wall and still have room for the L shaped couch and love seats. The Formal Dining Room adds an air of sophistication to this wonderful home. The ceilings are 9 feet tall throughout. The Great Room, Master bedroom, Foyer, and Formal Dining all have 10 foot tray ceilings. All the windows have custom fitted plantation shutters or blinds. The Master suite has His and Her custom closets, A sizable master bath (that has a huge! elegant walk-in shower with custom tile work and seating), double vanities and sinks. The home has many storage closets and a custom security system.     When you arrive at your new home you can pull up onto the apron of your custom paver drive and you can step out to your covered front porch. Next you walk through your leaded glass front double doors to enter the foyer of you new home. From the foyer you can see all the way out to the rear lanai. The large Den/Office on the left is a quiet retreat for your personal hobbies. To the right is the secondary bedroom area that has 2 mini-suite bedrooms with their own private baths, and large private baths. One bath has a custom walk-in shower and the other a bathtub/shower combo. They are perfectly suited for in-laws or visitors. There is also a large inside laundry/utility room with pre-plumbed connections for a large sink. Both gas and electric hookups are available in the laundry. This room leads to the 20x23 garage with custom overhead storage bins. In the back yard you have a natural gas hookup so if you want an outdoor kitchen you have the gas available. Or, possibly to add a gas heater to your to be built custom pool. You have access to multiple HOA resort style pools, workout centers, tennis courts, parks, walking trails, golf and the club house. Community HOA pays for high speed internet and basic cable services along with irrigation water via your custom irrigation system. Deland is a wonderful town with many great restaurants, shopping plazas, as well as community hospitals, and medical offices of all kinds. The Atlantic Beaches are 35 minutes away and the Disney Parks are only 50 miles South.    Seller says SELL!
